codex
The erasure changes add durable redaction tracking, but the new record-level excision and missing-sink handling can both let the engine report completion while telemetry redaction obligations remain unmet.

Full review comments:

- [P1] Refuse excising pending redaction records — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s5/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:7341-7344
  When `excise_collection_record` is aimed at the internal `erasure_pending_redaction` collection, it deletes the durable queue entry that tells retries which telemetry stable IDs still need redaction; `complete_erasure_at_rest` then sees no pending work and can report success while the telemetry sink still contains erased IDs. This can happen through the new CLI flags with `--excise-collection erasure_pending_redaction --excise-record-key <verb>`, so this internal collection needs to be rejected or otherwise protected here.

- [P2] Treat missing telemetry sink as incomplete redaction — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s5/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:7167-7170
  If a pending redaction exists but the telemetry sink path has been moved or rotated away, this `NotFound => Ok(())` path clears the pending queue as if the IDs were redacted, even though the old file may still exist under its rotated name with the erased `result_stable_ids`. In that scenario the erasure verb can return success without completing telemetry redaction, so `NotFound` should remain an `ErasureIncomplete` unless the engine can prove the sink was deleted rather than moved.
